
performs integer division of two 32-bit signed integers and
writes the quotient and remainder to standard output.

The dividend and divisor are defined at assembly time in the .data
section of divide.s.

REQUIREMENTS

  - GNU Assembler (as) 2.30+
  - GNU Linker (ld) 2.30+
  - Linux x86-64

BUILDING

  $ make

Output format: QUOTIENT R REMAINDER

LIMITATIONS

  - Division by zero causes SIGFPE
  - Maximum quotient: 10 digits (2^31-1)

